title: Politics
description: Post Politics from The Washington Post is the source for political news headlines, in-depth politics coverage and political opinion, plus breaking news on the biden administration and White House, Congress, the Supreme Court, elections and more.

title: Herschel Walker says abortion ‘nothing to be ashamed of,’ but supports ban
dc:creator: Amy B Wang
description: The Republican nominee for U.S. Senate in Georgia is denying the latest reports from the Daily Beast that he paid a former girlfriend to have an abortion — and that the woman is the mother of one of his children.

title: Post Politics Now: Biden heads to New York to herald IBM’s major investment in Hudson Valley
dc:creator: Amy B Wang
description: President Biden is heading to Upstate New York to tour IBM as the company promotes a $20 billion investment over 10 years in the Hudson Valley.

title: Herschel Walker poses an unusual test of the strength of partisanship
dc:creator: Philip Bump
description: The reeling Republican Senate candidate can, at least, rely on his party's eagerness to control the Senate.

title: Herschel Walker, and the GOP’s declining demand for morality in leaders
dc:creator: Aaron Blake
description: Republicans once demanded morality in their politicians. In the Trump era, not so much.

title: How the Supreme Court could give Republicans more power with elections
dc:creator: Amber Phillips
description: The Supreme Court is considering two election cases in Alabama and North Carolina that could give Republicans a lot more authority to shape elections.

title: How the GOP could win the Senate, despite itself
dc:creator: Aaron Blake
description: And despite Herschel Walker. A new poll distills a dynamic shaping the midterms: Despite voters expressing disapproval of some candidates, key races remain extremely tight.

title: Cheney urges Ariz. voters to reject GOP candidates for governor, secretary of state
dc:creator: Azi Paybarah
description: Rep. Liz Cheney (R-Wyo.) described Arizona gubernatorial nominee Kari Lake and secretary of state candidate Mark Finchem as threats to democracy.

title: Where Republican election deniers are on the ballot near you
dc:creator: Adrian Blanco
description: Nearly 300 Republicans on the ballot in 2022 midterms have disputed the 2020 election results. See which are running near you.

title: Veterans’ suicides decline but remain ‘unfathomable and unacceptable’
dc:creator: Joe Davidson
description: Despite the improving data, the 6,146 veterans’ suicides in 2020 equaled a daily average of almost 17, according to the Department of Veterans Affairs.

title: Biden, DeSantis meet in Florida, pledging bipartisanship on Ian relief
dc:creator: Toluse Olorunnipa
description: The president and the governor, potential opponents in the 2024 presidential campaign, put politics aside during the trip, instead focusing on the urgent matter of recovery from Hurricane Ian.

title: Post Politics Now: Biden tells hurricane-hit Florida that federal government ‘will be here until it’s finished’
dc:creator: John Wagner
description: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis (R) is considered a potential 2024 White House contender, and he and Biden have sparred on several issues. The White House said the visit will be "above politics."

title: Former Uber security chief convicted of covering up 2016 data breach
dc:creator: Joseph Menn
description: The case was the first brought against a corporate executive over a breach by outsiders. It also may be the last — the payoff that prompted the charges has become common practice in hacking cases.

title: 9 tips to debunk false claims made by friends and family
